@NODE Source "AGuide - The fellow programmers' section"

Source code
-----------

The  C source code of AGuide is included. It has been written for DICE
V2.07.54R.  You  will probbly have to adapt @{"start.c" link start.c/MAIN} for use with other
compilers.

@{"start.c" link start.c/MAIN}  is  some  glue  between  DICE's  _main()  and  the  IMHO more
reasonable calls to clistart() and wbstart().

@{"start.h" link start.h/MAIN} is the header file <pd/start.h> used by start.c.

@{"aguide.c" link aguide.c/MAIN}  is  the  main  source  code  file.  You  need the AmigaGuide
includes  <clib/amigaguide_protos.h> and <libraries/amigaguide.h> from
C='s AmigaGuide distribution to compile it.

You have to create stub routines for the amigaguide.library calls. See
comment in @{"aguide.c" link aguide.c/MAIN} on that topic.


    "There is not now, and never will be, a language in which it
     is the least bit difficult to write bad programs." - Flon's Law

@ENDNODE

